<p class=indbig>
<b>Why do I need a Handheld PC?</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
<b>Because you can&rsquo;t e-mail a napkin.</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
You never know when &ndash; or where &ndash; the light bulb is going to go on. 
When that perfect idea pops up and you need to capture it for later. Now you&rsquo;re 
covered with a Handheld PC running Microsoft&reg; Windows&reg; CE.
</p><p class=indbig>
For one, <b>it&rsquo;s light, turns on instantly and stays on for up to 12 
hours with one battery.</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
And two, it&rsquo;s your ideal PC Companion, complete with Pocket versions of 
your most-often-used desktop applications &ndash; Word, Microsoft Excel, PowerPoint, 
Microsoft Access, Outlook&reg;, and Microsoft Internet Explorer. They don&rsquo;t 
do everything your desktop PC can do, just what you need most when you&rsquo;re 
mobile. <b>Send e-mail. Take notes. Check your calendar. Browse the Web.</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
You can take all of your vital information with you, everywhere you go, and 
back again. Just connect your desktop PC with your Handheld PC, <b>and any changes 
are automatically updated between the two machines.</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
Handheld PCs come in a range of sizes, from a range of manufacturers, and start at 
$799. Purchase one today and receive a FREE<sup><small>*</small></sup> Kingston&reg; 
8MB CompactFlash&trade; storage card and bonus software &ndash; an over $100 
value. For a complete list of manufacturers and retailers, go to:
</p><p class=indbig>
<br><br>
www.microsoft.com/windowsce/hpc<br>
Microsoft&reg;<br>
Where do YOU want to go today?
</p>
